        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Donation<BR>Pronunciation: dO-'nA-sh&n<BR>Function: noun<BR>Etymology: Middle English donatyowne, from Latin donation-, donatio, from donare to present, from donum gift; akin to Latin dare to give <BR>: the act or an instance of donating : as a : the making of a gift especially to a charity or public institution b : a free contribution : GIFT<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Let me first say that I have no problem with druids in general. It's the few greedy uneducated ones that get to me. I rarely ever GG. I've only ever done it a few times and didn't have to pay 'cause the druid was my RL friend. Anyways the issue is the definition of a donation. Two similar instances have irked me.</P><P>You say out of character "Anyone offering a GG?"<BR>Player1 tells you "I am at mill"<BR>You tell Player1 "Ok omw and how much do you charge?<BR>...<BR>...<BR>You say "Hail Player1"<BR>Player1 invites you to join a group<BR>You have joined the group<BR>You tell your group "So how much do you want?"<BR>...<BR>...<BR>Player1 tells the group "Ok donate and we'll go."<BR>(I offer him 8pp. Maybe it's low but I really don't know and it is just a donation right? Not a fee.)<BR>You have been removed from group.<BR>You tell Player1 "What the hell? I ask you how much? You ask for a donation and then kick me out when I don't offer enough?"</P><P>Some days later similar setup</P><P>You say to the group "How much do you charge?"<BR>Player2 says "Who has donated?"<BR>Player3 says "I have"<BR>You say "I haven't yet. How much?"<BR>Player2 says "Make donation Sskeli"<BR>(so I give 10pp and she accepts)<BR>Player2 "Just to let you know Sskeli the going rate for donation is 20pp but I'm feeling nice today."<BR>/boggle</P><P><BR>Ummmm...these people need to get their lingo straightened out. Don't ask for a damn donation if you are expecting a fee.</P><P></P><P><br><BR>"...ashes...ashes...we all fall down."<BR><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/sskelisig25.gif" border=0></P><P></font></td>
