        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> <BR>     Lucky me I just happen to have a druid as well as a necro so I can post on this one. I also have melee classes that have needed ports as well and this has happened to me when I have tried to get a port. Sometimes believe it or not I can only donate 5 to 6pp to the druid skyways donation ride. I have never asked for a set price for 1 to 2 minutes of my time and I will continue not to, if anyone asks how much I usually say whatever you can afford whether its 5pp or 2pp and I would even take a rusty weapon or splitpaw hide belt if thats all you can offer. As long as its something to show me you appreciate my efforts. Usually all the money goes to anyway is spells or trade skills so its really no big deal if I only get 5pp for a port sometimes. Sure I would rather have 30pp but anyone who has ever had to sell batwings and bonechips at level 8 or 9 to get enough spell money knows its hard enough to be able to find a way to get money for a port at low levels unless you come across enough hq bear pelts to pay your way. So for all you druids out there, don't be a jerk and do this. If someone gives you 2pp just suck up your gut sigh and take them anyway. Maybe when you get there someone will be auctioning 100pp for a port and you can quit your whining. Also you won't look like such an arse which is always a plus because we druids have a tendency to have a bad wrap because more people play our class,which of course means more twits.</P><P>Fadorna Du'Pre<BR>Bonechiller of the 20th season<BR>Evil Unkempt Druid of the 43rd season<BR>Mana-chewer<BR>Rper</P><P>"Hmm, do I want red wine or white wine with your corpse"</P><P>Fadorna Du'Pre<BR>Scholar of Neriak<BR>House of Du'Pre<BR>Innoruuk's 3rd Mistress</font></td>
