 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Neurnoch</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Assuming this topic doesn't apply to absolute n00bs  whose sole intention is to solicit money for ports, one of the most efficient ways I get a port, which I do indeed often, is simply by asking. If you spice up the question, maybe RP it a little, and/or be very polite/funny/witty you will almost always get a port. I always offer a donation but 9 times out 10 it gets cancelled, and when it doesn't well...I just paid 40pp for 10 ports /shrug. Assuming again, we are talking about the fairly high end game....lvl 30's will almost always expect a donation. Again, the very major key is the way you ask, even if the porter is busy they will not usually consider the intrusive tell rude, but will simply inform you they cannot. Leave at that, and find another......with the exception of sending a tell to someone in PoG=) In fact, I've made many close porting friends by asking for ports in /tells in my ever-charming way /wink=)</P><P>-Neurnoch</P><P> </font></td>
